6 Section 3. Section 13-14-211, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "13-14-211. Judicial offices separate and independent offices for election purposes. (1) Each
8 vacancy for justice of the supreme court is a separate and independent office for election purposes. The chief
9 justice of the supreme court shall assign an individual number to the justices and certify these numbers to the
10 office of the secretary of state.
11 (2) Each vacancy for judicial office in a district that has more than one district judge is a separate
12 and independent office for election purposes.
13 (3) (2) Each vacancy for office in a county that has more than one justice of the peace is a separate
14 and independent office for election purposes."
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Transition. (1) [This act] may not remove any justice that is holding
17 office on [the effective date of this act] during the term for which the justice was elected or appointed. After [the
18 effective date of this act], the chief justice shall assign each sitting associate justice to the judicial district that
19 corresponds to the associate justice's current seat number and certify these numbers to the office of the
20 secretary of state, and the chief justice must be assigned to the seventh district.
21 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (2)(b), each supreme court justice who chooses to seek
22 reelection at the end of the justice's current term shall run for reelection in the district to which the justice is
23 assigned under subsection (1).
24 (b) A sitting justice that chooses to seek election in a district other than the district assigned under
25 subsection (1) may run for election in the district if the justice resigns the justice's current seat effect effective as
26 of the date the justice files for election in the district to which the justice seeks election.
27
